Comment: "{Attempts:5, Duration:0:15, Sessions:1}. Thought about topping out, but then my foot slipped and I figured that was a sign from my conscience to not be stupid."
"{Attempts:10, Duration:0:30, Sessions:1}. So after getting scared up high I found this gem in the guidebook with the description, "anyone enjoy lowballs?" I do. I love lowballs."
"{Attempts:1, Duration:0:01, Sessions:1}. Practicing my streetshoe roof skills."
"{Attempts:5, Duration:0:15, Sessions:1}. Hard in the streeshoes! Gotta go to the left hand with the right hand; mindblowing."
"{Attempts:1, Duration:0:01, Sessions:1}. Cutting my feet on slab! Always a good time!"
"{Attempts:15, Duration:1:30, Sessions:1}. Took an adventureous fall, and then did it first try once all the European people left."
"{Attempts:4, Duration:0:15, Sessions:1}. Meh. I think this boulder is the epitome of "okay"."
"{Attempts:20, Duration:1:30, Sessionss:2}. Couldn't quite finish in the dark back in 2014 but did it quickly this year after Mackenzie gave us all a lesson on the Flossing dance."
"{Attempts:5, Duration:0:30, Sessions:2}. Couldn't streetshoe it back in 2014. Crappiest of the Roadcrew Roof Tour, but still kind of fun."
"{Attempts:20, Duration:1:00, Sessions:1}. One move wonder where the one move isn't even fun. Five stars."
"{Attempts:20, Duration:1:00, Sessions:1}. Tricky and weird, but I kind of liked it. Shoutout to the Italian guys on Orange Heart giving it 100%."
"{Attempts:25, Duration:2:30, Sessions:1}. Really nice problem in a sweet setting. Only thing holding back the recommended flag is the sharpness of that right hand."

"{Attempts:4, Duration:0:30, Sessions:1}. Hard ass first move but a sweet second move. I love climbing obscure random problems that aren't that good and often very lowball. It's my main strength in climbing."
"{Attempts:2, Duration:0:10, Sessions:1}. Made virtually no progress on Ron Ron et Caramel so I did this instead."
"{Attempts:1, Duration:0:01, Sessions:1}. More streeshoe practice! This time in the down jacket and in the rain."
